kevmath: kevin's math library (very original name, yes, i know.)
(c) 1996-2002 Kevin Meinert


=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
Usage:
=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

everything is in the kev namespace:

kev::Quat         (templated for any datatype)
kev::Vec2         (templated for any datatype)
kev::Vec3         (templated for any datatype)
kev::Vec4         (templated for any datatype)
kev::Matrix4f     
kev::ColorRGBA

the template ones have typedefs for what they are (i.e. kev::Vec3f)

Defines.h 
defines a math portability layer (ie. kev::sin()), and common constants

convert.h 
supplies conversion funcs between the data types

extend.h
adds funcs that don't nessesarily belong in the classes...


=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
Build:
=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

you should be able to simply type:

  gmake
  
If this doesn't work, try to find out why, or copy the entire output to the
author of this project so they may debug it.  Describe your system and
compilers installed.


=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
Install:
=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

use the Makefile's install target.  
this target defaults to "./build" in the the current directory.  
you can set it to something different with the following:

   gmake install prefix=/mydir/whatever/blah


=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
history:
=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
originally started 1996 as f-lib (everything was prefixed by an f, no reason)
progressed rapidly in Iowa State Univiersity's computer graphics class (ME519)
progressed from there in various little prototype projects Ive done for amusement
This project isn't actively maintained by me anymore.  
- I've started a new project called GMTL (Generic Math Template Library)
- see ggt.sf.net, or search google, or contact me (in that order)..


